title: International Migrants to Canada Based on Gender and Age
name: International Migrants to Canada Based on Gender and Age

properties.table 051-0011 international migrants, b: Estimates of Population by Age and Sex for Canada, Provinces and Territories - 3604

properties.column_2: Data for persons aged 90 to 100 years and over will be available from 2001/2002.

The population growth, which is used to calculate population estimates, is comprised of the natural growth (CANSIM 51-0002 and 51-0013), international migration (CANSIM 51-0011) and interprovincial migration (CANSIM 51-0012).
The number of immigrants is final up to 2010/2011 and preliminary for 2011/2012.
Age -1 represents persons born after July 1 and not included in age group 0 to 4 years.
Data for Northwest Territories and Nunavut are presented separately from 1991/1992.
Prior to 1991/1992, only data for Northwest Territories and Nunavut combined are available.
